text: Gossner may refer to: ==People== * Ernst Gossner (born 1967), Austrian film director, screenwriter and producer * Johannes Gossner (1773–1858), German clergyman and philanthropist * Miriam Gössner (born 1990), German biathlete and cross-country skier ==Education== * Gossner Theological College, a Christian Theological Seminary in Jharkhand, India * Gossner College, a Christian college in Assam, India ==Other== * Gossner Foods, one of the largest cheese manufacturers in the United States, based in Logan, Utah
